# A larger graph specifically constructed so that the greedy / maximal-matching
# approximation algorithm performs significantly worse than optimal.
# 
# Structure:
# - A central triangle (1,2,3)
# - Three long paths (each length 20) branching from 1, 2, and 3
# 
# Optimal vertex cover ≈ 31
# Greedy matching algorithm returns ≈ 60+ (guaranteed non-optimal)

